article.description: Allison Hightower scored 18 points and had a career-high six steals Wednesday night, leading No. 11 Louisiana State to a 56-47 victory over 15th-ranked Xavier for coach Van Chancellor's 500th victory.
article.headline: Chancellor wins 500th; LSU moves to 11-1 by beating Xavier
article.linkText: LSU tops Xavier for Chancellor's 500th victory
article.story:
CINCINNATI -- Allison Hightower scored 18 points and had a career-high six steals Wednesday night, leading No. 11 Louisiana State to a 56-47 victory over Xavier (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) for coach Van Chancellor's 500th victory.

LSU (11-1) forced Xavier to turn it over 11 times while building a 35-25 halftime lead. It was the lowest-scoring half of the season for Xavier (9-3) to that point. The Musketeers could only manage 22 points in the second half.

Katherine Graham scored a career-high 14 points for LSU. A 3-pointer by Xavier's Katie Rutan cut the lead to 42-40 with 8:03 left, but the Musketeers couldn't get any closer.
